  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with a matching lid with 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and leave to steam-dry, uncovered, until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, quarter the <strong>pineapple slices</strong> (reserve the juice!)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pineapple</strong> and cook for 2-4 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1336.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, push the <strong>pineapple</strong>&nbsp;to the side of the pan and add the<strong> pork mince </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook the <strong>pork</strong> for 5-6 min, breaking it up with a spatula as you go&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
